tudy in particular that found that almost 7000 alameda county residents who routinely slept six or fewer hours a night had about a 70 percent higher risk of dying than did people of similar age who slept seven or eight hours a night read more search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest humphreys discusses the rebuilding of iraq's mental health care system june 1 2008 in the news take health advice with salt keith humphreys january 18 2008 san francisco chronicle babies brains and videotape keith humphreys san francisco chronicle on october 28 2007 a toast to your heart keith humphreys san francisco chronicle on july 1 2007 humphreys featured in news articles on work rebuilding iraq's mental health system chpintl in the news stanford report on august 8 2005 humphreys awarded research career scientist status by va system march 19 2004 news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
